'''多姆斯'''（domus）在[[拉丁語|拉丁語]]中是「家宅」或「家庭」之意。在[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]時期，多姆斯是上流階級和中流階級公民的住宅<ref>{{cite book |title = The Roman villa |url = https://archive.org/details/romanvillavillau0000will | last=Frazer| first= Alfred | publisher = University of Pennsylvania Museum Publication|year = 1998| pages = [https://archive.org/details/romanvillavillau0000will/page/64 64] | isbn= 978-0924171598 }}</ref>，廣泛分佈在羅馬帝國的各城市。現代英語中的「domestic」一詞即起源自多姆斯<ref>{{cite book |title = Daily life in the Roman city |url = https://archive.org/details/dailylifeinroman00aldr | last=Aldrete| first=Gregory S. | publisher = Greenwood Press|year =2004| pages = [https://archive.org/details/dailylifeinroman00aldr/page/75 75]| isbn=978-0313331749 }}</ref>。富裕的羅馬人除了在市區擁有多姆斯之外，還在郊外擁有[[羅馬別墅|羅馬別墅]]。特別是在羅馬帝國後期，在別墅居住的羅馬人增加，別墅的規模也越來越大，有的別墅還搭建圍牆，就像一座小城。經營階層的多姆斯大多裝飾華麗<ref>{{Cite web | url= http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Domus.html| title= Domus | accessdate=2009-04-28| publisher=LacusCurtius Educational Resource: a Selection of Articles from A 19th-Century Classical Encyclopaedia }}</ref>。與之相對的是平民階級的羅馬人只能住在[[因蘇拉|因蘇拉]]。
